title: Does US Need Free-Trade Deal With Europe?
description:
The proposed Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership would cut tariffs, standardize regulations and give American companies direct access to Europe. Many Democrats and labor activists say the deal will fall short of safety standards and hurt worker wages, but proponents of liberalized trade with Europe say the U.S. cannot afford to be left behind. VOA's Mil Arcega reports.
Originally published at - http://www.voanews.com/media/video/united-states-free-trade-deal-europe/2732524.html
tags: Europe', 'United States', 'wages', 'Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership', 'trade deal', 'safety standards'
